{
  "stem": "15721.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And therefore, they had a program of education that far exceeded what let's say high school students would, would cover in, in the, m contemporary Chicago.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they, they went deep into all kinds of mathematical problems already way beyond calculus and so on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he taught until 1936, when he was unwillingly put into pension because at that time, the Nazis had long already determined that Jewish teachers could no longer teach in German schools.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The reason he lasted that long was that he had been a decorated veteran of the First World War and as a veteran had been given certainly what you might call a protective privilege until 1936.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then he was pensioned.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very much so-- we had a very observant home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no question about kashrut.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was simply not even a question.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We never ate in a restaurant that I can recall.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We observed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We, we prayed daily together, my father, my brothers and I, especially after my having become a bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father and I, they'd fill in the morning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we doesn't gather each morning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Shabbos was kept very scrupulously.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I, for instance, decided after my bar mitzvah that I would no longer write on the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And therefore, my father petitioned my high school to relieve me from attending classes on the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because school was normally from Monday through Saturday in those days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was granted the opportunity to be absent because I was a fairly good student and they were quite sure that I could make up whatever I missed.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And of course, both Friday evening and Saturday morning, regularly without any fail, no matter where we were or what circumstances, we were in synagogue.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So yes, we were a very observant home.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
